OL,7,FTim Jarvis, director general of
OL,8,Fmarkets at Ofgem, said: "While today's
OL,9,Fchange means the cap has remained
OL,10,Frelatively stable, we understand that
OL,11,Fthe cost of energy remains a challenge
OL,12,Ffor too many households.
OL,14,F"Our reliance on volatile
OL,15,Finternational markets - which are
OL,16,Faffected by factors such as events in
OL,17,FRussia and the Middle East ` means the
OL,18,Fcost of energy will continue to
OL,19,Ffluctuate.
